| Pattern                     | Fundamentally about                                                     | When to use it                                                     | Typical use cases                                                            | Memory trick                                      | Java object / Java feature that feels similar                                                                                                     |
| --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Factory**                 | Creating the right object without exposing creation logic               | When object creation depends on type, config, env, or rules        | `VehicleFactory`, parser creation, DB client creation, notification creation | **Factory = object-making shop**                  | Static factory methods like `List.of()`, `Map.of()`, `Calendar.getInstance()`, `Executors.newFixedThreadPool()`                                   |
| **Abstract Factory**        | Creating families of related objects                                    | When one config/theme decides multiple related objects together    | Windows vs Mac UI widgets, cloud-specific clients, theme-based components    | **One factory creates a whole family**            | No single exact object; closest is a group of related interfaces + implementations, like JDBC driver families or UI toolkit families              |
| **Builder**                 | Constructing complex objects step by step                               | When many optional params or staged construction exist             | `HouseBuilder`, HTTP request builder, config builder                         | **Builder = assembling piece by piece**           | `StringBuilder`, `Stream.Builder`, many Lombok/manual builders, `HttpRequest.Builder`                                                             |
| **Singleton**               | Ensuring only one instance exists                                       | When exactly one shared instance should exist                      | logger, config manager, cache manager                                        | **Single = only one**                             | `Runtime.getRuntime()`, enum singleton pattern in Java                                                                                            |
| **Adapter**                 | Making incompatible interfaces work together                            | When external/legacy API does not match your interface             | Twilio wrapper, Stripe wrapper, legacy service integration                   | **Adapter = plug converter**                      | `InputStreamReader` adapts byte stream to character reader; `Arrays.asList()` also feels adapter-like                                             |
| **Facade**                  | Giving a simple interface over a complex subsystem                      | When subsystem is messy and you want one clean entry point         | `PaymentFacade`, `OrderFacade`, travel booking service                       | **Facade = front desk**                           | `java.nio.file.Files` gives simple methods over more complex file system operations                                                               |
| **Proxy**                   | Controlling access to another object                                    | When you want lazy loading, access control, caching, remote access | remote proxy, security proxy, virtual proxy                                  | **Proxy = stand-in / gatekeeper**                 | `java.lang.reflect.Proxy`, Spring AOP proxies, Hibernate lazy proxies                                                                             |
| **Decorator**               | Adding behavior without changing original class                         | When optional features should wrap core behavior                   | logging wrapper, retry wrapper, buffering, compression                       | **Decorator = wrapping gift paper**               | `BufferedInputStream`, `BufferedReader`, `DataInputStream`, `Collections.unmodifiableList()` feels wrapper/decorator-like                         |
| **Strategy**                | Choosing one behavior/algorithm from interchangeable options            | When same task has multiple algorithms                             | payment methods, discount rules, sorting, routing                            | **Strategy = choose the plan**                    | `Comparator`, `Runnable`, `Callable`, lambdas passed as behavior                                                                                  |
| **Template Method**         | Defining the skeleton of an algorithm, leaving some steps variable      | When process structure is fixed but some steps differ              | report generation, file parsing, ETL stages                                  | **Template = same recipe, different ingredients** | Abstract classes with final workflow method + overridable hooks; e.g. pattern commonly built with `abstract class` in Java                        |
| **Observer**                | Notifying many listeners when state changes                             | When one change should fan out to many subscribers                 | UI listeners, stock alerts, event systems                                    | **Observer = subscribers watching changes**       | `Observer/Observable` was old Java; modern equivalent is listeners, `PropertyChangeListener`, event listeners, reactive streams                   |
| **Command**                 | Encapsulating a request as an object                                    | When actions need queuing, retry, undo, scheduling                 | job queue, button action, undo/redo, task execution                          | **Command = action packed in a box**              | `Runnable`, `Callable`, `FutureTask`, executor tasks                                                                                              |
| **State**                   | Changing behavior based on internal state                               | When object behaves differently in different phases                | vending machine, order lifecycle, workflow states                            | **State = same object, different mood**           | Java `enum` plus state-specific methods, or separate state classes                                                                                |
| **Chain of Responsibility** | Passing request through handlers until one handles it                   | When request should flow through multiple processors               | servlet filters, auth middleware, approval chains                            | **Chain = pass it along**                         | Servlet `FilterChain`, Spring Security filter chain                                                                                               |
| **Mediator**                | Centralizing communication between many objects                         | When peer-to-peer object interaction becomes messy                 | chat room, dialog controls, workflow coordinator                             | **Mediator = traffic police**                     | `ExecutorService` is not exact, but a controller/coordinator object in Java code is the common mapping; event bus/coordinator classes are typical |
| **Bridge**                  | Separating abstraction from implementation so both vary independently   | When there are two changing dimensions                             | shape + renderer, message + sender, remote + device                          | **Bridge = connect two dimensions**               | Interface + composition, e.g. `MessageSender` inside `Notification`; not a single standard Java object, more of a design style                    |
| **Composite**               | Treating single objects and groups uniformly                            | When tree structures exist                                         | file system, UI tree, org chart, menu tree                                   | **Composite = part and whole treated same**       | `java.awt.Container` / component trees, recursive node structures using same interface                                                            |
| **Flyweight**               | Sharing common intrinsic data to save memory                            | When huge numbers of similar objects exist                         | text editor chars, game tiles, icons                                         | **Flyweight = share the common part**             | `Integer.valueOf()`, string pool, enum constants                                                                                                  |
| **Prototype**               | Creating objects by cloning an existing one                             | When cloning is easier than rebuilding                             | template docs, game entities, config snapshots                               | **Prototype = copy from sample**                  | `clone()`/`Cloneable` conceptually, though not loved in modern Java                                                                               |
| **Iterator**                | Traversing a collection without exposing internals                      | When collection traversal should be uniform                        | lists, trees, custom collections                                             | **Iterator = one by one walker**                  | `Iterator`, `ListIterator`, stream traversal                                                                                                      |
| **Memento**                 | Capturing and restoring object state                                    | When undo/history/checkpoint is needed                             | text editor undo, rollback, save state                                       | **Memento = memory snapshot**                     | No perfect built-in; closest is serialization snapshot or custom immutable state object                                                           |
| **Visitor**                 | Adding new operations to stable object structures without changing them | When structure is stable but operations keep growing               | compiler AST passes, export/report operations                                | **Visitor = new operation visits each type**      | No direct built-in; often implemented with interfaces + overloaded `visit()` methods                                                              |
